Tip

In an ordered pair of numbers, the first number is the x-value and is found on the horizontal axis. The second number is the y-value and is found on the vertical axis.

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

Equations can be solved by adding the same number, or term, to both sides of the equation, subtracting the same number (or term) from both sides of the equation or by multiplying both sides of the equation, or dividing both sides of the equation by the same number or term.

success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Algebra, Function and Patterns / Simplifying

review_1.column_1_text:
Solution

3a and 4b are unlike terms. 3a + 4b cannot be simplified.

Tip

Like terms are terms that have exactly the same pronumeral part. Only like terms can be added or subtracted.

review_3.column_1_text:
Tip

When multiplying, if the base is the same, add the indices. When dividing, if the base is the same, subtract the indices. When raising a power to a power, multiply the indices.

review_3.column_1_text:
The points (1, 3) and (5, 7) lie on the line.

The y-values are two more than the x-values.

The equation is y = x + 2.

Tip

Each point lying on a line obeys a particular rule. This rule is called the equation of the line. This question could have been answered by substituting both of the points into each equation to see which one was satisfied by both.
